          <div type="positioning">
            <p xml:space="preserve">
              <geo>35°82′N 10°64′E</geo>
            </p>
          </div>
          <div type="typology">
            <p xml:space="preserve">Dialect group: Maghreb, Tunisia</p>
            <p xml:space="preserve">Urban sedentary dialect, Sāḥil group</p>
          </div>

          <div type="general">
            <p xml:space="preserve">Sousse is an important coastal city in the west of Tunisia which
              has been a regional trade centre for many centuries. Starting in
              the 1960s Sousse has developed into one of the country’s main
              Tourism destinations. This caused immense increase in population,
              especially migration from rural areas all over Tunisia, which has
              significantly influenced the original dialect.</p>
          </div>

          <div type="researchHistory">
            <p xml:space="preserve">A detailed study on the dialect spoken within 
              the medina is <rs type="bibl" ref="zotero:VNHH49Z2">Talmoudi 1980</rs>, a
              collection of texts can be found in <rs type="bibl" ref="zotero:NP7ZI6PP">Talmoudi 1981</rs>. An
              analysis of verbs of Romance origin in Tunisian dialects,
              including data from Sousse, is given in <rs type="bibl" ref="zotero:5WDMXBJ9">Talmoudi 1986</rs>. 
              <rs type="bibl" ref="zotero:G5R6TQS8">Saada 1956</rs> is a study
              about the dialect of the Jews of Sousse.</p>
          </div>

          <div type="bibliography">
            <p xml:space="preserve">Get the full list of publications on the dialect of Sousse in our
              database by clicking <rs type="bibl" ref="bibl:geo:Sousse">here</rs>. </p>
          </div>
